<item>
            <title>[HBASE-6139] Add troubleshooting section for CentOS 6.2 page allocation failure issue</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6139</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Tim Robertson reports:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;HBase CentOS version 6.2 reports kernel: java: page allocation failure. order:4, mode:0x20. Any ideas anyone?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;echo 360448 &amp;gt; /proc/sys/vm/min_free_kbytes appears to stop page allocation failure using HBase on CentOS 6.2&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If this is the proper fix for this condition, we should document it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@Tim, how did you arrive at 360448?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
